.TH man 3 "27 October 2020" "1.0" "_printf man page"
.SH NAME
.B _printf
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "holberton.h"
.PP
int printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B _printf "()
Function produces output according to a format.
.PP
The function writes to
.I stdout
.PP
_printf() takes a pointer to an array, and a variable list of arguments.
.PP
it iterates every character of the array and copies it to the standard output,
.B when a "%" symbol is reached,
the function checks if it's a format specifier, so it will check if the next character is an 's' (for string), 'c' (for character), 'i' or 'd' (for numbers). If it's true, then it will call the respective function to format the arguments passed by the va_list.
.SH CONVERSION SPECIFIERS
After a '%' is reached in the string, then it will check if the next character is:
.PP
.RS
.B % - Prints a literal '%' symbol
.PP
.B s - String specifier, expects an array of characters, prints every character except the null byte
.PP
.B c - Character specifier, will take a character as an int and print it
.PP
.B d, i - Number specifier, takes an int and process it while printing every single number as a character
.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon successful return, the function will return the total number of characters printed (except the null byte used to end strings)
.SH BUGS
Unknown
